==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Loaf
<hw>Loaf</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Loaves</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE. <ets>lof</ets>,
<ets>laf</ets>, AS. <ets>hl⟦amac⟧f</ets>; akin to G. <ets>laib</ets>,
OHG. <ets>hleip</ets>, Icel. <ets>hleifr</ets>, Goth. <ets>hlaifs</ets>,
Russ. <ets>khlieb'</ets>, Lith. <ets>kl⟦eum⟧pas</ets>. Cf.
<er>Lady</er>, <er>Lammas</er>, <er>Lord</er>.]</ety> <def>Any thick
lump, mass, or cake; especially, a large regularly shaped or molded
mass, as of bread, sugar, or cake.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Loaf sugar</b></col>, <cd>refined sugar that has been
formed into a conical loaf in a mold.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loaf</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Loaf
<hw>Loaf</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Loafed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Loafing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[G. <ets>laufen</ets> to run,
Prov. G. <ets>loofen</ets>. See <er>Leap</er>.]</ety> <def>To spend time
in idleness; to lounge or loiter about.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ <xex>Loafing</xex>
vagabonds.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>W. Black.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loaf</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Loaf
<hw>Loaf</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To spend in idleness; -- with
<ptcl>away</ptcl>; <as>as, to <ex>loaf</ex> time away</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loafer</ent>⟦br⟧
